One newsletter issue for 1988. For issue 33, see: OREXT-N-89-003. The name of the newsletter changed to Ocean and Coastal Law Memo and is now under the Oregon Sea Grant Extension Program.

The Ocean Law Memo is an aperiodic publication of the University of Oregon Ocean Resources Law Program (ORLP) and is distributed by the OSU Extension Service, Sea Grant Marine Advisory Program. at the University of Oregon Law School in Eugene, Oregon. The ORLP is supported in part by the U. S. The following topic is in this issue: Recent Developments in Ocean and Coastal Law, 1987.
